H.B. 1170
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 30, 2026
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40659-MCa-316
Short Title: Funding for Winston-Salem. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative K. Brown.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR A COMMUNITY CENTER LOCATED IN
3 WINSTON-SALEM.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
6 Budget and Management the sum of two hundred ten thousand eight hundred dollars ($210,800)
7 in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to Bodegas
8 Alvarado, Inc., a nonprofit organization, to assist in the completion of converting an abandoned
9 industrial center into a community center suitable for multiple purposes, including recreation and
10 sports, located in the City of Winston-Salem.
11 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
*DRH40659-MCa-316*

